<br>
Even though they were kinda lame, GM events used to be very cool. People would run half-way across the world to attend and all of the EQ fan sites would list them and the results after they happened. This was one way where VI could have kept a non-static content going but dropped the ball. It went the way of CS. Instead of enriching the gameplay of the product they had they put all of their energy into adding to it. If I had to choose between lame GM events where a bunch of killer chickens invade the Dreadlands and nothing, I would choose lame GM events.<br>
Vulrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustrayvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stray VZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 2:36:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wannabebigforums.com/avatar.php?userid=2617&dateline=1027035878 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI's Failure</span><hr size=1> GM events where great...but soon where ruined by bickering and the &quot;uber&quot; guilds coming in and taking over as soon as they had found out about them.<br>
