<br>
1. A fairly rich and detailed backstory that is learned in as bits and pieces here and there throughout the game.  Coupled with a game world that doesn't force you into any particular storyline.<br>
<br>
2. A website that details all the rich history of the world and which is basically required reading to understand what the point of the game is.  An on-going storyline which you will be thrust into the moment the game starts, and have no chance to affect.<br>
<br>
The second option is the approach Neocron, Shadowbane, and Asherons Call 2 are taking.  There's nothing wrong with that, but playing a forced role in someone else's story isn't how I want to roleplay.  It's too much like playing Diablo or Final Fantasy; no matter what you do, the story is going to proceed through a pre-determined and already-written plot. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubreoghan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Breoghan</A> at: 9/28/02 4:17:17 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.0.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href=http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html>JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

